# Monday GraphQL Best Practices

## Patterns to Flag

- Queries requesting all fields without specifying needed columns (`column_values` without `ids` filter)
- Missing `limit` on `items_page`, `boards`, or paginated queries
- Using deprecated `items` field instead of `items_page` with cursor pagination
- Nested queries deeper than 3 levels without complexity checks
- Queries inside loops without batching (N+1 query patterns)
- Missing error handling on GraphQL responses (not checking `errors` array)
- Hardcoded board/item IDs in production code (should be configurable)

## What to Do

- Always specify `limit` on paginated queries (default varies, explicit is safer)
- Use `items_page` with `cursor` for pagination, not `items` with `page`/`limit`
- Filter `column_values` by `ids` to only fetch needed columns
- Add `complexity { before after reset_in_x_seconds }` to monitor query cost
- Batch related queries into a single GraphQL request when possible
- Check for `errors` in every API response before accessing `data`
- Use variables for IDs and dynamic values instead of string interpolation

## Exceptions

- Schema introspection queries (which necessarily request broad type info)
- One-off scripts or CLI tools where performance is not critical
- Queries using `all_monday_api` MCP tool (which handles pagination internally for some operations)
